HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin Ta Bayar Da Rahoton Ƙaruwar Yawan Masu Cutar A China Da Kashi 14
China ta ba da rahoton ƙaruwar kashi 14 cikin ɗari na mutanen da ke rayuwa da cutar kanjamau ko kuma AIDS.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce fiye da mutane 820,000 ne suke fama da wannan cuta a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu kimanin sabbin kamuwa da cutar 40,000.
Sabanin yadda aka saba a baya, mafi yawan sabbin cututtukan an samu ne ta hanyar jima'i.
A dā, cutar HIV ta yaɗu da sauri a wasu ɓangarorin ƙasar Sin ta wajen ƙarin jini da aka yi da cutar.
Amma, adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin da ke wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, a shekara guda, adadin mutanen da suke da cutar HIV da AIDS a China ya ƙaru da 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a tsakanin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
A shekarar 1997, an sake yin amfani da laifin luwadi a kasar Sin, amma ana nuna wa 'yan LGBT' yanci.
Saboda tsananin ra'ayin mazan jiya a kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza sukan auri mata.
Yawancin kamuwa da cututtuka na faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya a lokacin jima'i a cikin waɗannan alaƙar.
A shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin HIV ga kowa da kowa don magance matsalar.
