Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da zalunci ta hanyar tallafin farfaganda
Bayan mako guda da jaridar hukuma ta kasar Sin ta wallafa wata sanarwa mai shafi hudu a wata jaridar Amurka, inda ta bayyana fa'idojin da cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China ke da shi, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi babban birnin kasar Beijing da amfani da jaridun Amurka don yaɗa labarai.
Amurka: A ranar Laraba da ta gabata, Donald Trump ya yi tsokaci kan takardar talla da aka wallafa a cikin jaridar China Daily da ke cikin jaridar Des Moines Register, wadda ita ce jaridar da ta fi yawan bugawa a jihar Iowa, bayan da ya zargi China da yin katsalandan a zaben shugaban kasa da aka yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, zargin da China ke musun yi.
Zargin da Trump ya yi wa Beijing na cewa ta yi kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya yi daidai da abin da jami'an Amurka suka shaida wa Reuters, wani sabon mataki na wani kamfen da Washington ta kaddamar don matsa wa China lamba.
Yayin da yake da kyau gwamnatocin kasashen waje su rika tallatawa domin bunkasa tattalin arzikin su, Beijing da Washington na cikin wani gagarumin rikicin kasuwanci, inda suka sanya wa juna takunkumin haraji kan kayayyakin da suke shigowa da su.
Tallafin da China ta yi wa 'yan kasuwar da suka goyi bayan jam'iyyar Trump a jihohi kamar Iowa, ya kamata ya shafi masu fitar da kayayyaki zuwa kasashen waje, in ji masana a China da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa na dogon lokaci, wanda ke fitar da kayan gona da yawa zuwa China, ya bayyana cewa Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikata, masu gonaki da kamfanoni.
China, in ji Branstad a cikin wani bayani a cikin Des Moines Register na ranar Lahadi, yanzu ta ninka wannan zalunci ta hanyar yin tallan farfaganda a cikin 'yan jaridar Amurka.
Ta hanyar yada farfagandar, gwamnatin China tana kalubalantar al'adun Amurka na 'yancin faɗar albarkacin baki da kuma 'yancin manema labarai, ta hanyar sanya tallace-tallace da aka biya a cikin Des Moines Register, in ji Branstad.
"A bambance, za ku ga wasu ƙididdigar ƙididdiga a kan kantunan jaridu a nan Beijing, kuma ba za ku ga ainihin bambancin ra'ayi da Sinawa za su iya yi game da ci gaban tattalin arzikin China ba, saboda gaskiyar cewa kafofin watsa labarai suna cikin hannun Jam'iyyar Kwaminis ta China", in ji shi.
Ya kara da cewa, daya daga cikin manyan jaridun kasar Sin ba ta amince da tayin da aka yi mata ba, amma bai ambaci sunan jaridar ba.
'Yan Republican sun janye mata masu jefa kuri'a daga zaben fidda gwani kan Kavanaugh, masu sa ido sun yi gargadi
Da yake da yawa daga cikin manyan 'yan Republican suna goyon baya da kare dan takarar kotun koli, Brett Kavanaugh, a yayin da ake zarginsa da aikata laifukan da suka shafi lalata, masu lura da al'amura sun yi gargadin cewa za a iya samun mummunan sakamako a lokacin zaben tsakiyar shekara mai zuwa, musamman daga mata.
Yanayin ya kasance mai matukar tashin hankali, kuma mafi yawan 'yan Republican sun riga sun sanar da cewa za su ci gaba da yin zabe.
"Ba za a iya dawo da irin wannan ba", in ji Grant Reeher, farfesa a fannin kimiyyar siyasa a Makarantar Maxwell da ke Jami'ar Syracuse, a wani labarin da aka buga a ranar Asabar.
Reeher ya ce yana shakkar cewa matakin da Sanata Jeff Flake (R-Arizona) ya dauka na minti na karshe na FBI zai kwantar da hankalin masu zabe.
"Mata ba sa manta da abin da ya faru a jiya, ba sa manta da abin da zai faru gobe, ba sa manta da abin da ya faru a watan Nuwamba", in ji Karine Jean-Pierre, mai ba da shawara ga mata kuma mai magana da yawun ƙungiyar MoveOn a ƙasar, a ranar Juma'a, in ji jaridar Washington, D.C.
A ranar Juma'a da safe, masu zanga-zanga a harabar majalisar dattijai sun yi ta ihu "November na zuwa!" a yayin da 'yan jam'iyyar Republican da ke da iko a kan kwamitin shari'a suka yanke shawarar ci gaba da tsayawa kan zaben Kavanaugh duk da cewa Dakta Christine Blasey Ford ta yi ikirarin cewa ta yi hakan, in ji Mic.
Stu Rothenberg, mai lura da al'amuran siyasa da ba ya son kai, ya ce, "Jimillar da ake samu a cikin dimokuraɗiyya da kuma motsawarsu, suna da muhimmanci sosai.
Mutane sun ce ya riga ya yi yawa, wannan gaskiya ne.
Amma zai iya zama mafi girma, musamman ma a tsakanin mata masu jefa ƙuri'a a cikin unguwannin bayan gari da kuma tsakanin matasa masu jefa ƙuri'a, mutane masu shekaru tsakanin 18 zuwa 29, waɗanda ko da yake ba sa son shugaban, amma ba sa yawan jefa ƙuri'a.
Ko da kafin jawabin da Ford ya yi a bainar jama'a inda ta yi bayani dalla-dalla kan zargin da ta yi wa dan takarar kotun koli na cin zarafin mata, masu lura da al'amura sun nuna cewa za a iya samun wani martani idan 'yan Republican suka yi magana a kan batun.
"Wannan lamari ne da ya kawo cikas ga jam'iyyar GOP", in ji Michael Steele, tsohon shugaban kwamitin Republican, a farkon makon da ya gabata, kamar yadda NBC News ta ruwaito.
"Ba wai kawai batun kuri'ar kwamitin ba ne, ko kuri'ar karshe, ko kuma dubawar Kavanaugh, amma kuma game da yadda 'yan Republican suka yi da kuma yadda suka yi da shi", Guy Cecil, darektan Priorities USA, wata kungiya da ke tallafawa zaben 'yan Democrat, ya fada wa News Channel.
Amma dai, Amurkawa sun nuna rashin amincewa da wanda za su yarda da shi bisa ga abin da Ford da Kavanaugh suka ce, tare da samun karin goyon baya ga na biyun.
Wani sabon binciken da YouGov ya yi ya nuna cewa kashi 41 cikin 100 na mutanen da aka yi hira da su sun amince ko kuma sun yarda da abin da Ford ya ce, yayin da kashi 35 cikin 100 suka ce sun amince ko kuma sun yarda da abin da Kavanaugh ya ce.
Bugu da ƙari, 38% sun ce sun yi imanin cewa Kavanaugh ya yi ƙarya ko kuma ya yi ƙarya game da shaidarsa, yayin da 30% suka ce haka game da Ford.
Bayan da Flake ya matsa wa FBI, The Guardian ta ba da rahoton cewa FBI na binciken zargin da Ford da kuma aƙalla ɗaya daga cikin waɗanda suka yi ƙarar, Deborah Ramirez suka yi.
A makon da ya gabata, a gaban kwamitin shari'a na majalisar dattawa, Ford ta bayar da shaida a gaban kwamitin shari'a cewa a lokacin da ta ke da shekaru 17, Kavanaugh, wanda ya sha giya ya yi mata fyade.
Ramirez ta yi zargin cewa dan takarar da ke neman a yanke mata hukunci ya nuna mata al'aurarsa a wajen wani biki da suka yi a lokacin da suke karatun digiri a jami'ar Yale a shekarun 1980.
