An girmama firist Bernard Vann, wanda ya ɗauki Victoria Cross a Yaƙin Duniya na ɗaya
A cikin shekara 100 bayan haka, an ba wa wani limamin cocin Ingila wanda ya yi yaƙi a Yaƙin Duniya na Ɗaya lambar yabo ta Victoria Cross a garinsu.
A ranar 29 ga Satumba, 1918, an ba da lambar yabo ga Lieutenant Colonel Bernard Vann, wanda ya yi aiki a lokacin da ake kai hari a Bellenglise da Lehaucourt.
Amma bayan kwana huɗu da ya yi hakan sai wani ɗan harbi ya kashe shi, kuma bai san cewa an ba shi lambar yabo mafi girma a yaƙin da ya yi a ƙasar Ingila ba.
A ranar Lahadi, 'ya'yansa biyu sun buɗe wani dutse a lokacin da ake yin bikin tunawa da shi a birnin Rushden da ke lardin Northamptonshire.
Ɗaya daga cikin jikokin, Michael Vann, ya ce wannan aikin yana da alamar alama, tun da aka buɗe dutsen tunawa daidai shekaru 100 bayan aikin jaruntakar da aka ba kakansa.
A cewar jaridar The London Gazette, a ranar 29 ga Satumba, 1918, Lieutenant Colonel Vann ya jagoranci rundunarsa ta wuce Canal de Saint-Quentin, ta hanyar hazo mai yawa da kuma bin bindigogi da bindigogi.
Daga baya ya shiga cikin layin wuta kuma ya jagoranci layin gaba da "mafi girman jaruntaka" kafin ya ci gaba da bindiga daya da ya kashe uku daga cikin sojojin.
An kashe Lt. Col. Vann a ranar 4 ga Oktoba, 1918, a hannun wani ɗan harbi na Jamus; fiye da wata ɗaya kafin ƙarshen yaƙin.
Michael Vann, mai shekara 72, ya ce abin da kakansa ya yi ya sa shi baƙin ciki da kuma baƙin ciki.
